<br>
I had a few ideas but not quite sure.<br>
Wurmslayer<br>
Veno axe<br>
Centi Longsword<br>
<br>
what do you guys think of those, and do you have any other ideas?<br>
<br>
I play on Prexus.<br>
<br>
Talabus Sunraii<br>
30 Half Elf Warrior <br>
Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzalot>Kilzalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/6/02 7:54:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4346.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Reasonable Upgrades?</span><hr size=1> Could always buy a Lammy. /shrug  Go hang out in ME and listen for Goranga Clubs rotting.  Those seem to rot all the time.  Or save your pennies and try for a Frosty.  IMHO your doing damn good for lvl 30 right now...  MUCH better than what I had at that level. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132589">Veteran Kilzalot Drachonis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=335271">Rubik Dashammybot</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hyardgune>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 9:22:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4346.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Reasonable Upgrades?</span><hr size=1> Avoid the wurmy, get yourself some one handers that are not slashing.  I'll assume you have about 4k to spend since you said 2k per.<br>
<br>
Keep the Centi Short<br>
get a Jade Mace<br>
get a piercer with 25 or less delay<br>
get a cheap 2hs like a Nathsar<br>
get a Sarnak Battlehammer<br>
<br>
Should come up to under 4k and you can then use these weapons to boost your skills in all of your melee abilities, rather than being yet another warrior who reaches the 50s and realizes that they were stupid because they only used 1hs... <p>Hyardgune Varangian<br>
59 Ogre Myrmidon<br>
Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 9:45:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4346.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Reasonable Upgrades?</span><hr size=1> I might drop the crystalline for a Jagged Blade of Mourning and put it in your main hand.<br>
<br>
Other than that, you are doing fine.  If you want to be more versatile, try for the Goranga Club, but that's wasting time kicking around a zone and trying not to get killed so the choice is yours. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dumeshuhlbelk>Dumesh UhlBelk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 317<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 12:11:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4346.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/w/i/wilsonua/DumStare.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Reasonable Upgrades?</span><hr size=1> Jade Mace + Jarsath Trident<br>
<br>
If you can get a wurmslayer in addition to those weapons, go for it, but know that by the late 40s you will want to unload the wurmslayer. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 10,10,900><b>Korak Sarathai - Barbarian Warlord - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"alt = "Dumesh's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 900,10,10><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thefrug>The Frug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 2:47:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4346.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Reasonable Upgrades?</span><hr size=1> Wurmslayer demolishes those other weapons until the mid 40's. At that point even, a Goranga Spiked Club (free in ME) outdamages a Jade Mace until level 52 I believe.<br>
<br>
So, if it were me, I'd go cheap (and effective) and save money because the plat in your bank now will be worth more in a couple of months than it is right now.<br>
<br>
Sell both of your current weapons<br>
<br>
1hs<br>
Buy a Wurmslayer 900p<br>
<br>
Pierce<br>
Jarsath Trident (11/22) 300-400p<br>
or<br>
Shaded Dagger (11/22) 400p<br>
<br>
1hb<br>
Shaded Staff (10/22) 200-250p<br>
<br>
2hs <br>
Nathsar Greatsword (17/30) 50-100p<br>
<br>
2hb<br>
Sarnak Battlehamer (30/40) 100p<br>
<br>
Using the Wurm and one of the 11/22 piercers as your steady regular combo you'll be doing great. <br>
<br>
